  • Classes in org.jfree.chart.block used by org.jfree.chart
    Class
    Description
    AbstractContentBlock
    A convenience class for creating new classes that implement the ContentBlock interface.
    Arrangement
    An object that is responsible for arranging a collection of Blocks within a BlockContainer.
    ArrangeParams
    A class for holding parameters to pass to the arrange() method in the Block class.
    ArrangeResult
    Represents the result of a call to one of the arrange() methods in the Block class.
    Block
    A block is an arbitrary item that can be drawn (in Java2D space) within a rectangular area, has a preferred size, and can be arranged by an Arrangement manager.
    BlockContainer
    A container for a collection of Block objects.
    ContentBlock
    A block that has content surrounded by padding, a border and a margin.
    RectangleConstraint
    A description of a constraint for resizing a rectangle.
